id: pm-b1ni
title: "pm validate --check-files misclassifies existing directories as deleted (GH-203, prune/auto-fix data-loss path)"
description: "GH-203: src/cli/commands/validate.ts:1287 marks a linked path missing when stats.isFile() is false, so existing DIRECTORY links (accepted by pm files --add) classify as deleted. Because --prune-missing and --auto-fix act on deleted classifications, they would remove valid directory links (data loss). Regression scope: GH-184 feature shipped v2026.6.12 (pm-0v2m). Fix: treat stats.isDirectory() as present (or distinct directory classification excluded from prune), plus repro test with linked dir. Repro in GH-203 confirmed against 2026.6.12."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[3]: "area:validate",gh-triage-2026-06-12,regression
created_at: "2026-06-12T16:11:23.630Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-12T16:56:01.070Z"
author: maintainer-agent
resolution: Fixed validate --check-files to treat existing directory links as present.
expected_result: Existing project directory links remain linked and are not pruned as missing.
actual_result: Existing directory link src passed isolated validate --check-files and focused/unit/coverage gates.
